  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nEnhancement request: Add the `--beacon-nodes` flag as an accepted parameter for `lighthouse account validator exit`\r\n\r\n## Rationale\r\n\r\nThis is a QoL change for my eth-docker tool. I have a user request to support splitting the consensus client and validator client to separate machines. Eth-docker gets the beacon node location from a user-specified variable. If the user sets `https://mymachine,https://infurabeacon` because they want fallback, then this will work great for the validator client, and not at all for exits. I'd need to ask the user for a separate variable that only contains one of the two for exits. With this enhancement in, one variable will work both for day-to-day attesting as well as exits.\r\n",
