    "body": "@yorickdowne, we had a look at implementing this in Lighthouse and our feeling is that introducing fall backs here introduces too much complexity in Lighthouse to warrant the convenience to the CLI.\r\n\r\nTo work around your problem, you could use [shell parameter expansion](https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/html_node/Shell-Parameter-Expansion.html) to extract only the first endpoint. Here's an example:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nENDPOINTS=https://mymachine,https://infurabeacon\r\necho lighthouse account validator exit --beacon-node ${ENDPOINTS%,*}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlighthouse account validator exit --beacon-node https://mymachine\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you wanted to exit on *all* endpoints (not just the first) you could use a bash script that iterates through each of the `ENDPOINTS` and runs the same command for each ([example on stack overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27702452/loop-through-a-comma-separated-shell-variable)).\r\n\r\nIn the interest of keeping the open-issue-count low, I'll close this for now. Please feel free to reopen if my suggested work-around doesn't work for you @yorickdowne :slightly_smiling_face: ",
